<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="776" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 M Nielsen, Niels/1:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden (<persName type="from">Myers</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-12T13:00:00+08:00">April 12, 1933—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 12—6:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>According to a telegram from Mrs. Nielsen, Doctor Niels Nielsen, an
                            American citizen and member of Danish Lutheran Mission stationed at
                            Siuyen was kidnapped last night and ransom of yuan 500,000 demanded.</p>
                        <p>Kidnapping informally brought to the attention of Japanese consular and
                            military authorities and of local authorities and their assistance
                            requested.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Myers</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>